data.description: In 1990, two years after being famously scouted by Sarah Doukas for her then new model agency Storm, Kate Moss signed an exclusive contract with Calvin Klein for apparel and fragrance. The move changed the face of modelling forever with Moss" petite proportions making a marked contrast to the Supers – Naomi Campbell, Linda Evangelista, Cindy Crawford et al – who dominated the ad billboards of the time.
data.title: April 1992

data.description: She was photographed with then boyfriend Mario Sorrenti by Andrew Macpherson - the image accompanied a feature on London style.
data.title: March 1993

data.description: A 19-year-old Moss was shot for her first cover of British [i]Vogue[/i] by model-turned-photographer Corinne Day, whom she met soon after signing with Storm models and who shared her passion for vintage clothes. With prophetic cover lines, Moss was proclaimed the face of “London Style”.
data.title: March 1993
